sentences: Hans Karl Ferdinand John (born 7 September 1936) is a German musicologist and former university professor.
He was a member of the Dresdner Kreuzchores from 1946 until his Abitur in 1954.
He was a member of the Dresdner Kreuzchores from 1946 until his Abitur in 1954.
In 1961 he was awarded his doctorate under Fritz Reuter at the Faculty of Philosophy in Berlin with the dissertation Music education in ancient Greece and its relevance for our time.
He then worked for 25 years at the Hochschule für Musik Carl Maria von Weber Dresden as a lecturer and professor of musicology.
In 1993 he was appointed director of the Institute for Musicology at the Dresden university.
John's research focuses on historical musicology of the 19th century, the music history of Dresden, Protestant church music and the Romantic music.
